b'Nedbank and Ranyaka are excited to announce that Buco Hardware, a division of The Building Company, is embarking on a journey with us as we tackle Fix Your Space and Land & Property projects that will help create spaces where people can prosper \xe2\x80\x93 in every sense of the word.

This year Buco has committed to helping with four projects in collaboration with Ranyaka in the Western Cape, where Buco has a relatively wide store footprint. These projects form part of the Nedbank Proud of My Town programme, for which Ranyaka is the implementation partner. This is an example of corporates joining forces around a shared vision to bring about positive change. #NedbankCares #ProudOfMyTown'

b"World Food Day is an opportunity for us as proud Nedbankers to raise awareness and take action for those who suffer from hunger and are most vulnerable. Today as we join forces with @foodforwardsa in their initiative for #ZeroHunger, we also stand by the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals of reducing overall hunger (SDG #2) and creating awareness of responsible food production and consumption through minimising food waste (SDG #12). \r\n\r\nSays Cobus de Bruyn, Northern Divisional Manager for #NedbankAgric: \xe2\x80\x98We are excited to, once again, partner with @foodforwardsa \xe2\x80\x93 this time physically helping to pack much-needed food for vulnerable communities. We\xe2\x80\x99ve been blown away by the scale of the organisation and the meaningful impact it has on the food security situation in South Africa'. #WorldFoodDay2020"

b'#WorldRhinoDay2020 celebrates all species of rhinoceros,  which are threatened due to illegal trade in rhino horn. Today we commemorate and stand with those who dedicate their lives to saving, conserving and protecting this precious wildlife species.

This day also brings together rhino reserves, grassroots organisations, zoos, and concerned individuals across the globe to raise awareness and support for the five species of rhinoceros.

b'The #ProudOfMyTown team has been witnessing the power of connection in a time of distancing; collaboration in a time of isolation and even amid lockdown, the unlocking of new networks.

As the harsh impact of lockdown regulations continue to expose and often worsen the many inequalities within our society, there are still diamonds to be found in the dust and dirt amid the Covid-19 crisis.

Many exciting new initiatives have emerged in response to the growing need for food security, and the \xe2\x80\x98new normal\xe2\x80\x99 has created fertile ground for mobilising communities to support those who cannot afford food. 

One such diamond can be found in the Farming for the Future initiative currently being piloted in the community of Klapmuts, just outside Stellenbosch. @ranyaka_community #NedbankCares'

b'We work in partnership with communities that face immense challenges and obstacles every day.\n\n#ProudOfMyTown  programmes include Community Safety, Early-childhood Development, Strong Schools and Building Business (entrepreneurial and enterprise support). b"The #ProudofMyTown Covid-19 food relief intervention in Mamelodi township was the first initiative tackled by the programme's implementing agent, @ranyaka_community, in collaboration with the South African Army Spouses Forum (SAASFO) assisted by the SA Army. \nSoldiers assisted local churches with the delivery of food parcels for 70 vulnerable households. The partnership has since been further strengthened through the involvement of the SA Army in subsequent food distribution initiatives in Polokwane and Nelspruit. \nWe would like to congratulate SAASFO for the critical role they are playing in responding to the pandemic in South Africa. #NedbankCares"

b'#ProudofMyTown  implementation agent, Ranyaka, is acting as the aid agent for Stellenbosch Unite Aid Action by coordinating the distribution of some 2 000 food parcels a week to households affected directly by the Covid-19 pandemic.
